The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Sunday, June 24, 2007

 Auto Fair

 Attend The Telegraph Auto Fair at 22 Camac Street, noon to 9pm. 

 Bong Connection 

 Listen to celebrities interact on, Cinematic Classic Then and Now Bong Connection, at Cafe Coffee Day, Lake Road, 3pm. 

 Eye on Art

 Browse through paintings and drawings of Kalighat and works by Jamini Roy at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3pm to 8pm. 

 Check out drawings and paintings by Tapan Chattopadhyay at Academy of Fine Arts, 3pm to 8pm. 

 Go through tapestry and serigraphy by S.H. Raza, at Gallery K2, 3.30pm to 7.30pm. 

 Book Release

 Be there at the release of The Phobic And The Erotic, edited by Brinda Bose and Subhabrata Bhattacharya, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 6.30pm. 

 Song amp; dance

 Groove to the tunes of Bollywood Dreams, at Vidya Mandir auditorium, 10.30am. 

 Enjoy Evening of Glory, a musical programme by Nandanik, at GD Birla Sabhagar, 6pm. 

 Watch an Odissi performance by Behala Sinjini, at Behala Sarat Sadan, 5.30pm. 




